IRS990.MissionDesc: THE ORGANIZATION PROMOTES BUSINESS INTERESTS AND ECONOMIC AND WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT IN THE GREATER SCRANTON AREA OF LACKAWANNA COUNTY.
IRS990.Desc: THE GREATER SCRANTON CHAMBER OF COMMERCE IS A MULTIFACETED MEMBERSHIP BASED BUSINESS ORGANIZATION THAT TOUCHES NEARLY EVERY ASPECT OF OUR COMMUNITY. OUR MISSION IS TO ATTRACT, SUSTAIN, AND GROW BUSINESSES THROUGHOUT NORTHEASTERN PENNSYLVANIA.IN ADDITION TO TRADITIONAL CHAMBER SERVICES, SUCH AS NETWORKING, REFERRALS, AND COST-SAVING PROGRAMS, THE CHAMBER IS ALSO THE PARENT ORGANIZATION TO VARIOUS AFFILIATES AND INITIATIVES THAT INCLUDE: THE SCRANTON-LACKAWANNA INDUSTRIAL BUILDING COMPANY (SLIBCO), THE SCRANTON PLAN, LACKAWANNA INDUSTRIAL FUND ENTERPRISE (LIFE), SLIBCO UTILITIES, THE IGNITE PROGRAM, METROACTION, LEADERSHIP LACKAWANNA AND SKILLS IN SCRANTON.THESE AFFILIATES AND INITIATIVES SUPPORT ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT, PROVIDE SMALL BUSINESS LENDING SERVICES, FACILITATE LEADERSHIP DEVELOPMENT PROGRAMS, AND GUIDE WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT INITIATIVES IN THE GREATER SCRANTON REGION. THE CHAMBER FAMILY SUPPORTS OUR MEMBERS' SUCCESS, CREATING OPPORTUNITIES FOR THE REGION AND HELPING BUSINESS OWNERS AND EXECUTIVES ADDRESS THE ISSUES THEY FACE EACH DAY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CHAMBER AND ITS SUBSIDIARIES ARE EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAXES UNDER PROVISIONS OF SECTION 501(C) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE FINANCIAL ACCOUNTING STANDARDS BOARD GUIDANCE ON ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES, MANAGEMENT EVALUATED THE CHAMBER AND ITS SUBSIDIARIES TAX POSITIONS AND CONCLUDED THAT THE CHAMBER AND ITS SUBSIDIARIES HAD TAKEN NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT REQUIRE ADJUSTMENT TO THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS TO COMPLY WITH THE PROVISIONS OF THIS GUIDANCE. WITH FEW EXCEPTIONS, THE CHAMBER AND ITS SUBSIDIARIES ARE NO LONGER SUBJECT TO INCOME TAX EXAMINATIONS BY THE U.S. FEDERAL, STATE OR LOCAL TAX AUTHORITIES FOR YEARS BEFORE JUNE 30, 2020.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 WAS REVIEWED BY THE AUDIT COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AT A FORMAL MEETING ON NOVEMBER 8, 2023, AT WHICH TIME THE COMMITTEE VOTED AND RECOMMENDED THE APPROVAL OF THE 990 SO LONG AS THE FULL BOARD HAS THE OPPORTUNITY TO REVIEW THE DOCUMENT PRIOR TO FILING. THE DOCUMENT WAS DISTRIBUTED TO THE FULL BOARD AND WAS ACCEPTED AT THE NOVEMBER 17, 2023 FULL BOARD MEETING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BOARD MEMBERS SIGN AND DISCLOSE ANNUAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST. DOCUMENTS ARE REVIEWED BY AN A VETTING COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS TO DETERMINE ANY SIGNIFICANT CONFLICTS. ALL CONFLICTS ARE DISCLOSED TO THE FULL BOARD FOR REVIEW AND COMMENT. ANY POTENTIAL QUESTIONABLE RELATIONSHIPS ARE FURTHER INVESTIGATED AS NECESSARY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION ANNUALLY ENGAGES A PERSONNEL COMMITTEE MADE UP OF INDEPENDENT BOARD MEMBERS TO REVIEW THE PERFORMANCE OF AND RECOMMEND TO THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE THE COMPENSATION OF THE PRESIDENT/CEO. THE PRESIDENT/CEO DETERMINES APPROPRIATE COMPENSATION FOR ALL OTHER PERSONNEL WITHIN THE ORGANIZATION - WITH THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE DULY INFORMED OF SUCH DETERMINATIONS. THE ORGANIZATION HAS ON A RECURRING BASIS ENGAGED A THIRD PARTY TO PROVIDE ANALYSIS OF INDUSTRY APPROPRIATE COMPENSATION FOR ALL MANAGEMENT LEVEL POSITIONS. COMPENSATION DECISIONS ARE BASED ON THESE STANDARDS AND A REVIEW OF THE ORGANIZATION'S ACCOMPLISHMENTS WITH RESPECT TO A BOARD APPROVED ANNUAL PROGRAM OF WORK, AND MANAGEMENT OBJECTIONS ESTABLISHED BY THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GOVERNING DOCUMENTS ARE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.

FOR THE YEAR ENDED JUNE 30, 2023, THE ORGANIZATION UTILIZED THE AUDIT COMMITTEE TO REVIEW THE FINANCIAL STATEMENT AUDIT AND FORM 990 AND THEN PROVIDED COPIES TO THE FULL BOARD FOR REVIEW AND FINAL APPROVAL.
